Package cs2030.simulator

Class SimState

  • java.lang.Object
    • cs2030.simulator.SimState
  • public class SimState
extends java.lang.Object
    This class encapsulates all the simulation states. There are four main components: (i) the event queue, (ii) the statistics, (iii) the shop (the servers) and (iv) the event logs.

                double serviceRate,
                double restRate,
                double restChance,
                double custChance)
        New constructor to instantiate the start of the simulation.
        Parameters:
        seed - The base seed for the RNG.
        noServer - Number of human servers for this simulation.
        noCheckout - Number of Self-Checkout servers for this siumulation.
        noQueue - The waiting queue size limit for this simulation.
        noCustomer - Number of customers in this simulation.
        arrivalRate - The arrival rate of customers.
        serviceRate - The service rate at which the customers are served.
        restRate - The resting rate of the human servers.
        restChance - The probability a human server goes to rest.
        custChance - The probability a customer is greedy.

      • simulateServerBack

        public SimState simulateServerBack​(double time,
                                   Server server)
        Simulate when a human server is back from his rest to start serving any waiting customer in his queue or take in any new customer.
        Parameters:

        server - The human server which is resuming service from its break.
        Returns:
        A new state of the simulation where the human server serves a waiting customer or goes into idle state.

      • processArrival

        private SimState processArrival​(double time,
                                Customer customer)
        Handle the logic of finding idle servers to serve the customer, or a server that the customer can wait for, or leave. Checks if the customer are greedy and process according to their following logic.
        Parameters:
        time - The time the customer arrives.
        customer - The customer to be served.
        Returns:
        A new state of the simulation.

      • simulateDone

        public SimState simulateDone​(double time,
                             Server server,
                             Customer customer)
        Simulates the logic of what happened when a customer is done being served. The server either serve the next customer or becomes idle. For the human server, it can go on break if the resting chance generated is less than the desired simulation rest chance.
        Parameters:
        time - The time the service is done.
        server - The server serving the customer.
        customer - The customer being served.
        Returns:
        A new state of the simulation.

      • serveCustomer

        public SimState serveCustomer​(double time,
                              Server server,
                              Customer customer)
        Handle the logic of server serving customer. Once the customer is served, a new done event is generated and scheduled.
        Parameters:
        time - The time this customer is served.
        server - The server serving this customer.
        customer - The customer being served.
        Returns:
        A new state of the simulation.

      • run

        public SimState run()
        The main simulation loop. Repeatedly get events from the event queue, simulate and update the event. Return the final simulation state.
        Returns:
        The final state of the simulation.
